ype>` to `Promise<ModelType \\| null>` across main implementation and 22 test declaration files to reflect the method's actual behaviour of returning null for missing items.|\n|**JoplinData test suite** <br> `packages/lib/services/plugins/JoplinData.test.ts`|Added new Jest test suite verifying `itemType()` returns `ModelType.Note` for existing notes, `ModelType.Folder` for existing folders, and `null` for non-existent item IDs.|\n|**Build artefact ignore patterns** <br> `.eslintignore`, `.gitignore`|Added `packages/lib/services/plugins/JoplinData.test.js` to ignore lists for generated test artefacts.|\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 4</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (4 passed)</summary>\n\n|               Check name              | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                                       |\n| :-----------------------------------: | :------- | :---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|              Title check              | ✅ Passed | The title accurately summarizes the main change: fixing potential TypeErrors in three methods by adding null checks and updating type signatures.                                                                 |\n|           Description check           | ✅ Passed | The description is well-related to the changeset, clearly explaining the problem, solution, test plan, and AI assistance disclosure for the null-handling fixes.                                                  |\n|           Docstring Coverage          | ✅ Passed | No functions found in the changed files to evaluate docstring 